<dl id="n42019b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42019b">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42019b"> 19(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> priest&apos;s footwater / purifies</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Chapter VII. Should auricular confession be tolerated among civilized nations?]</font> The idolators of India believe that they will be purified from their sins by drinking the water with which they have just washed the feet of their priests. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 81</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
